                        "displayName": "Dennis Day",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I have attached a revised version of FormLabel.php for testing and review.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dennisatddddesigns",
                        "name": "dennisatddddesigns",
                        "displayName": "Dennis Day",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-08T12:27:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-08T12:27:23.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35230",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The patch as provided will not work, as it makes the invalid assumption that the form is assigned to the view as the variable \"form\".\r\n\r\nA better approach would be to modify the FormLabel view helper to allow suppression of the \"for\" attribute via an options flag, and passing that option from the decorator.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-15T08:20:31.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-15T08:20:31.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35231",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Resolved in trunk and 1.9 release branch.\r\n\r\nFormLabel view helper now has a \"disableFor\" option. If enabled, no \"for\" attribute will be created. Zend_Form_Element_FormRadio now sets this option by default.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
